    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "\"It depends\"\n\nThe easiest way would be to put grpc work on a separate thread.\n\nStepping up from there, you could have a different grpc_endpoint that uses libev... and every time there's IO on that endpoint follow up with a poll to a completion queue (the synchronous c++ api's won't work).\n\nIf you're ambitious, an iomgr port to libev ought to be possible. If you wanted to do that work, we'd probably take it as a contribution and make it an option for users.\n"
